Executive Profile
Peter B. Thompson  Executive VP & COO, TiVo CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships48$2,281,195As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Peter B. Thompson, also known as Pete, Co-founded Bizible, Inc. and serves as its Chief Technology Officer. Mr. Thompson has been the Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President of TiVo Corporation since September 6, 2016. He manages a global organization of engineering, sales, marketing, operations and customer support teams defining the future of home entertainment through the development of television products that appeal to consumers, producers and carriers ... alike. He is also responsible for Ericsson’s portfolio of full-featured TV Platforms for managed networks including the Mediaroom, Multiscreen (MMP) and Content Management System (CMS) product lines. He has more than 20 years of experience in building new businesses and product categories across a range of industries and technologies. He served as a Senior Vice President of the Mediaroom Business Group at Ericsson Corporation from 2013 to 2015. He served as the Corporate Vice President of Ericsson's Mediaroom Division. He served as General Manager of Microsoft Surface. He was at T-Mobile as Executive Director of HotSpot and he served in several roles with increasing responsibility at HP. He served as Corporate Vice President of Microsoft TV Division since 2012. He served as Vice President of Product Partnering of Sonos, Inc. from 2015 to 2016 and also served as its Vice President of Strategic Partnerships. He joined Ericsson with the acquisition of Microsoft Mediaroom. He served as Vice President of Microsoft Mediaroom. Mr. Thompson has extensive market awareness, knowledge and experience. Since joining Microsoft in 2006, his successes included the development of a breakthrough in Natural User Interface with Microsoft Surface and leading the largest gaming and social network in the living room with Xbox LIVE. During his seven year tenure at Microsoft, he helped develop and scale a number of high-profile initiatives including the Microsoft Surface large form-factor computer and the Xbox LIVE global entertainment service. Before joining Microsoft, he developed new products and services at T-Mobile, Graviton, Hewlett-Packard, Motorola and Levi Strauss & Co. He has been a Director of The E. W. Scripps Company since May 2, 2017. He has been an Independent Director of Sigma Designs, Inc. since December 23, 2013. He has been a Director of SeaWell Networks Inc., since April 2013. Mr. Thompson earned a Bachelor's Degree in International Economics at UCLA and a Master's Degree in Management from the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University.Read Full Background




